  "text": "Gene expression was quantified using RSEM as described above. Isoform ratios were quantified using two distinct methods. First, MISO was used to quantify isoform ratios for alternative splicing events contained in MISO's v2.0 annotations. Second, novel alternative splicing or intron retention of annotated constitutive splice junctions was quantified using reads crossing the 5′ or 3′ splice sites as previously described [CITATION_1] . Differentially spliced events were defined as those with at >20 identifying reads (identifying reads support one or more, but not all, isoforms of a splicing event), a change in isoform ratio ≥10%, and a Bayes factor ≥5 (computed with Wagenmakers's framework [CITATION_2] ).",
